data.description: Do you love Craftsman Style Homes? Well, you're in luck. This Beauty is ready for a new owner. She has been well taken care of the last 18 years but her current owners are looking to downsize. Let's take a stroll up the sidewalk past the beautiful mixture of lilies, roses, Lantana's and Rose of Sharon and step on to the large, covered porch. As you enter you will see a large living area with hardwood floors, tall ceilings. Adjacent to it is the large dining room with intricate wood details in its doorway and hardwood floors. Kitchen is a wide galley kitchen with a dishwasher, fridge on one side and sink on the other and a Gas Stove that has its own little spot. There's ample storage cabinets and counter space as well. Bedrooms are large and they have great closet and storage space. Bathroom is in the hall but there's entry from the main bedroom. Laundry room is spacious and located in the back of the Home and also serves as a sitting area. Small porch attached to the back of the home. Backyard is fenced and there are 2 storage buildings that will stay.
